179
00:11:24,610 --> 00:11:27,120
You almost got me killed!

180
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:30,850
Well, you almost died once anyway,
you blue-nosed oaf!

181
00:11:30,850 --> 00:11:33,590
Leave my blue nose out of this!

182
00:11:44,730 --> 00:11:46,020
Doctor...

183
00:11:46,020 --> 00:11:46,700
Hm?

184
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:50,980
This is... the first time
I've fought with someone.

185
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:56,990
That makes sense. To fight,
you need to have an opponent.

186
00:11:56,990 --> 00:11:59,950
Then... is it your first time
for this as well?

187
00:12:03,390 --> 00:12:04,540
Hm?

188
00:12:05,690 --> 00:12:09,330
I offer you this gift
to commemorate our making up.

189
00:12:09,990 --> 00:12:13,000
A gift...? Making up...?

190
00:12:21,670 --> 00:12:25,270
Life is hard for outcasts
like us, isn't it?

191
00:12:25,890 --> 00:12:28,770
But don't hold a grudge
against humans.

192
00:12:28,770 --> 00:12:31,730
This country is sick right now.

193
00:12:31,730 --> 00:12:34,850
The king and his people suffer
from a sickness of the heart.

194
00:12:34,850 --> 00:12:38,720
Some would probably say
that you can't heal a sick country,

195
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:39,740
but that's not true.

196
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:44,200
Once my invention is complete,
this country will be saved!

197
00:12:44,960 --> 00:12:49,330
There used to be a master thief
in a country far to the west.

198
00:12:49,330 --> 00:12:52,710
He had a serious heart disease.

199
00:12:52,710 --> 00:12:55,940
He sought treatment from every
skilled doctor he could find

200
00:12:55,940 --> 00:12:58,570
but none could fix him.

201
00:12:58,570 --> 00:13:03,080
Being told he would die unsettled him,
but then he passed by a mountain.

202
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:07,390
There... he saw a sight
that he had never seen in his life.

203
00:13:15,990 --> 00:13:17,150
Cherry blossoms!

204
00:13:17,150 --> 00:13:20,650
He saw vivid cherry blossoms
all over the mountain!

205
00:13:20,650 --> 00:13:24,370
After that, he went to see
another doctor and was shocked

206
00:13:24,370 --> 00:13:26,100
because the doctor said,

207
00:13:26,100 --> 00:13:28,740
"You have a clean bill of health."

208
00:13:28,740 --> 00:13:29,620
What?

209
00:13:29,620 --> 00:13:33,580
He was all better! You're thinking
it must've been some miracle, right?

210
00:13:33,580 --> 00:13:35,650
But it was definitely medical science!

211
00:13:35,650 --> 00:13:39,840
A powerful emotion somehow
triggered a change in the man's body!

212
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:44,890
That means there's no disease
in this world that can't be cured.

213
00:13:44,890 --> 00:13:50,260
No matter what anyone says about me,
I'll save this country as a doctor!

214
00:13:51,470 --> 00:13:57,630
That's why I raised this skull
and crossbones against all diseases!

215
00:13:57,630 --> 00:13:58,570
A skull...

216
00:13:58,570 --> 00:14:03,940
This here... is a symbol of conviction
that defies the impossible!

217
00:14:03,940 --> 00:14:07,450
I'll save this country as a doctor!

218
00:14:07,450 --> 00:14:12,040
By raising this flag,
I'll fight just like pirates do!

219
00:14:12,040 --> 00:14:15,040
Hey! Reindeer!

220
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:17,590
Join us and become our friend!

221
00:14:17,590 --> 00:14:21,440
Hm? Whoa! That looks so good!

222
00:14:27,020 --> 00:14:29,310
It's cool to be a pirate!

223
00:14:29,750 --> 00:14:32,600
Doctor, what are pirates?

224
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,230
Pirates?

225
00:14:34,870 --> 00:14:37,740
Pirates are remarkable people
who roam the seas.

226
00:14:37,740 --> 00:14:40,380
They have large, muscular
bodies and eagle eyes.

227
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:42,900
Their voices are like thunder
splitting the sky!

228
00:14:43,550 --> 00:14:46,320
Are you... really a pirate?!

229
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:46,740
Hm?

230
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:49,720
Yeah, I am...

231
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:54,080
Like I've been saying, join us!
It's fun to be a pirate! Pirates sing, too.

232
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:57,210
What? Th-They sing?

233
00:14:57,960 --> 00:15:01,030
Yeah. And they dance, too!

234
00:15:01,030 --> 00:15:02,930
You call that being a pirate?!

235
00:15:02,930 --> 00:15:04,930
Yep! And there are lots of adventures.

236
00:15:05,430 --> 00:15:08,640
Adventures? So pirates
go on adventures then?

237
00:15:09,140 --> 00:15:12,680
Of course! Pirates risk their lives
to go on adventures!

238
00:15:12,680 --> 00:15:14,890
You can meet lots of amazing people!

239
00:15:14,890 --> 00:15:17,150
Pirates are incredible!

240
00:15:17,150 --> 00:15:20,900
There are countless people
like that out at sea!

241
00:15:21,450 --> 00:15:24,290
Chopper, go out to sea some day.

242
00:15:24,290 --> 00:15:28,690
If you do, you'll realize
just how small your own problems are.

243
00:15:28,690 --> 00:15:34,040
Compared to the rest of the world,
your home island is this small!

244
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:35,500
Really?

245
00:15:35,500 --> 00:15:39,790
No, it's smaller! Like this! It's true!

246
00:15:43,910 --> 00:15:47,260
Your future lies beyond that sea!

247
00:15:48,380 --> 00:15:52,470
The good times passed
in the twinkling of an eye.

248
00:15:53,140 --> 00:15:54,890
But eventually...

249
00:16:02,660 --> 00:16:05,320
the time to bid farewell...

250
00:16:06,630 --> 00:16:08,820
comes for everyone.

251
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:15,450
It took a whole year,

252
00:16:13,740 --> 00:16:17,660
One Year Later

253
00:16:15,450 --> 00:16:17,660
but your treatment has finished.

254
00:16:17,660 --> 00:16:20,630
Your injuries are
completely healed, Chopper.

255
00:16:20,630 --> 00:16:23,750
Yes! Thank you, Doctor!

256
00:16:23,750 --> 00:16:25,960
Well then... take care.

257
00:16:26,780 --> 00:16:27,880
What?

258
00:16:29,090 --> 00:16:32,220
Now, go! Live as you please!
I'm busy with my research!

259
00:16:33,100 --> 00:16:37,100
I no longer have any moral obligation
to take care of you!

260
00:16:38,630 --> 00:16:43,900
Doctor! I'll never cause any trouble again,
so please let me back in!

261
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:47,740
I'll give you daily shoulder massages!
I'll brew tea and clean the house!

262
00:16:47,740 --> 00:16:49,820
Please! Let me stay!

263
00:16:51,910 --> 00:16:55,370
I don't have any friends!
I have no place to go!

264
00:16:58,880 --> 00:17:02,420
Doctor! Doctor!

265
00:17:04,290 --> 00:17:08,400
Doctor! Doctor!

266
00:17:10,090 --> 00:17:11,220
Chopper!

267
00:17:14,960 --> 00:17:19,180
Look, Doctor, I'm injured.
Hey, Doctor!

268
00:17:20,140 --> 00:17:22,150
Look!

269
00:17:25,740 --> 00:17:27,690
Why... Doctor?

270
00:17:27,690 --> 00:17:31,410
Go! Go out to sea! Go anywhere!

271
00:17:31,410 --> 00:17:33,410
But don't ever come back here!

272
00:17:48,630 --> 00:17:51,040
Forgive me, Chopper!

273
00:17:56,980 --> 00:18:01,440
I'm... going to die soon.

274
00:18:02,730 --> 00:18:05,230
Yeah, you will.

275
00:18:05,230 --> 00:18:08,530
Tell me. How much longer do I have?

276
00:18:08,530 --> 00:18:11,060
Oh? If you're asking me
to examine you, I refuse.

277
00:18:11,060 --> 00:18:13,780
You don't have the money
to pay my fee.

278
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:17,080
Tell me!

279
00:18:22,870 --> 00:18:26,020
How do you plan to kill me
with a tranquilizer gun?

280
00:18:27,710 --> 00:18:31,220
Fine, I'll tell you. You'll die
ten days from now at five o'clock.

281
00:18:31,220 --> 00:18:33,120
You won't have to suffer any more.

282
00:18:33,120 --> 00:18:35,760
Ten days... That'll be enough.

283
00:18:35,760 --> 00:18:37,600
I only need two days...

284
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:41,160
In two days, I will complete
my thirty-year-long research project.

285
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:44,690
I will... make cherry blossoms
bloom in this country!

286
00:18:44,690 --> 00:18:49,630
Cherry blossoms? So that research
you've continued for thirty years

287
00:18:49,630 --> 00:18:52,070
was about making
cherry blossoms bloom?

288
00:18:52,070 --> 00:18:57,070
The miracle cherry blossoms that saved you,
a master thief, long ago?

289
00:18:57,070 --> 00:18:58,280
That's right!

290
00:18:58,280 --> 00:18:59,490
What?

291
00:19:00,810 --> 00:19:04,780
Foolish man. This is a winter island
where it's bitter cold year-round.

292
00:19:04,780 --> 00:19:06,880
Cherry blossoms won't bloom here.

293
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:08,210
They will!

294
00:19:08,210 --> 00:19:14,340
I was just a thug hanging on to life by a thread,
but my heart changed as I kept on living.

295
00:19:14,340 --> 00:19:18,050
Every human in this world
can be saved!

296
00:19:18,050 --> 00:19:22,220
I'd like to prove it here on Drum,
the land where I was born!

297
00:19:22,220 --> 00:19:27,710
Listen. What you're attempting
isn't medicine or anything like it.

298
00:19:27,710 --> 00:19:32,630
Even if cherry blossoms bloom,
it will do nothing for human bodies.

299
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:34,980
Hiriluk!

300
00:19:40,350 --> 00:19:46,620
Chopper... we're alike.
So before I die, I'd like to teach you...

301
00:19:47,460 --> 00:19:49,690
that nothing in this world is impossible.

302
00:19:49,690 --> 00:19:52,730
You can accomplish
anything and everything!

303
00:19:52,730 --> 00:20:00,050
But the story of these two
doesn't have a happy ending.

304
00:20:00,050 --> 00:20:02,640
Why?!

305
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:05,190
Wait! Wait, wait, wait, wait!

306
00:20:05,190 --> 00:20:07,650
Wait!

307
00:20:13,210 --> 00:20:14,280
That smell...

308
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:15,110
Huh?

309
00:20:15,640 --> 00:20:16,820
Wapol!

310
00:20:21,480 --> 00:20:24,380
When he found out that Hiriluk
had only ten days to live,

311
00:20:24,380 --> 00:20:27,620
Chopper was very upset.

312
00:20:27,620 --> 00:20:30,280
Well, that was only natural.

313
00:20:30,280 --> 00:20:34,440
But he took action in his own way...

314
00:20:45,390 --> 00:20:48,020
I'm... going to die soon.

315
00:20:49,340 --> 00:20:52,900
I will... make cherry blossoms
bloom in this country!

316
00:20:56,010 --> 00:21:01,110
This here... is a symbol of conviction
that defies the impossible!

317
00:21:05,120 --> 00:21:08,860
What's going on?
Many guards have been absent lately.

318
00:21:08,860 --> 00:21:12,500
Well... they're out picking mushrooms
at the request of the Issie 20.

319
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:13,730
Mushrooms?

320
00:21:13,730 --> 00:21:19,370
They said there's some mushroom
that can cure anything...

321
00:21:19,370 --> 00:21:20,720
Mushroom?

322
00:21:20,720 --> 00:21:21,260
Ah!

323
00:21:21,260 --> 00:21:21,840
Hm?

324
00:21:22,340 --> 00:21:24,940
Bonehead! They'll see us!

325
00:21:24,940 --> 00:21:27,580
Doctor, about what they said...

326
00:21:46,870 --> 00:21:49,750
I'm not going to shoot you!

327
00:21:51,080 --> 00:21:53,500
But don't ever come back here!

328
00:22:03,590 --> 00:22:06,470
I treated you terribly.

329
00:22:06,470 --> 00:22:10,230
Wait until you can see
my cherry blossoms.

330
00:22:10,230 --> 00:22:13,580
They'll be my final accomplishment.

331
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:28,790
Well... here we go again!

332
00:22:47,700 --> 00:22:51,700
Dammit! I don't have much time left!

333
00:23:12,910 --> 00:23:16,370
Nothing's impossible when a man
raises a skull and crossbones flag!

334
00:23:16,370 --> 00:23:18,880
That's what I told you, right?!

335
00:23:23,270 --> 00:23:24,970
I will fight!

336
00:23:24,970 --> 00:23:27,420
Just like pirates do!

337
00:23:39,460 --> 00:23:42,230
I found it! The amiudake.

338
00:23:42,230 --> 00:23:44,760
That's the one!

339
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:46,570
But...

340
00:23:48,370 --> 00:23:50,950
How do I get across?

341
00:24:02,340 --> 00:24:04,510
One Week Later

342
00:24:11,320 --> 00:24:13,720
Dammit!

343
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:25,130
Doctor...

344
00:24:25,900 --> 00:24:33,240
I'm sorry... I lost...
one of your precious books.

345
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:36,260
What... happened to you?

346
00:24:37,040 --> 00:24:38,670
Mushroom...

347
00:24:41,150 --> 00:24:42,250
Medicine...

348
00:24:42,250 --> 00:24:44,630
That's an amiudake!

349
00:24:45,670 --> 00:24:49,160
You... got it for me?

350
00:24:49,160 --> 00:24:52,830
Please live... Please live, Doctor.

351
00:24:52,830 --> 00:24:57,580
I wanna be a doctor.
Please teach me how to become one.

352
00:24:58,540 --> 00:25:01,770
I'll fight, too... just like pirates do!

353
00:25:05,940 --> 00:25:08,070
Can a reindeer become one too?

354
00:25:10,320 --> 00:25:14,660
You can! You can! You can!

355
00:25:14,660 --> 00:25:17,020
You can be a great doctor...

356
00:25:17,020 --> 00:25:19,020
Doct... I can't breathe.

357
00:25:19,860 --> 00:25:23,380
...because you have such a kind heart.

358
00:25:25,840 --> 00:25:28,240
You bonehead!

359
00:25:32,140 --> 00:25:34,800
Chess! Kuromarimo!

360
00:25:34,800 --> 00:25:37,520
Is the doctor hunt going well?!

361
00:25:34,850 --> 00:25:37,520
King Wapol
Drum

362
00:25:37,520 --> 00:25:38,770
Yes sir.

363
00:25:37,560 --> 00:25:42,230
Chess
Drum Councilor
Kuromarimo
Drum Bailiff

364
00:25:38,770 --> 00:25:41,140
We've exiled most of the doctors already.

365
00:25:41,140 --> 00:25:42,230
Most?

366
00:25:42,230 --> 00:25:45,460
However, two have eluded capture.

367
00:25:42,270 --> 00:25:45,460
Dalton
Drum Royal Guard Captain

368
00:25:45,460 --> 00:25:47,860
That Dr. Kureha and...

369
00:25:47,860 --> 00:25:50,320
...the quack, Hiriluk.

370
00:25:50,320 --> 00:25:52,280
What'd you say?!

371
00:25:53,950 --> 00:25:56,650
Oh, yeah! I've come up
with a good idea!

372
00:25:56,650 --> 00:25:56,910
– Hm?
– Hm?

373
00:25:56,910 --> 00:26:04,830
Send an official notice to the citizens.
The Issie 20 have all... fallen ill.

374
00:26:05,700 --> 00:26:08,390
How is the amiudake soup?
Is it good?

375
00:26:08,390 --> 00:26:10,740
Ahh! Damn, this tastes terrible!

376
00:26:10,740 --> 00:26:11,240
What?!

377
00:26:11,240 --> 00:26:14,410
No living thing could stomach this!

378
00:26:14,410 --> 00:26:15,710
Oh no...

379
00:26:15,710 --> 00:26:19,350
Don't be so down. Medicine isn't
supposed to taste good.

380
00:26:19,350 --> 00:26:21,730
That means it's working.

381
00:26:21,730 --> 00:26:24,230
Thank you, Chopper.

382
00:26:27,430 --> 00:26:28,300
Huh?!

383
00:26:28,300 --> 00:26:29,030
Wha...?

384
00:26:32,570 --> 00:26:34,030
Huh?

385
00:26:38,040 --> 00:26:39,140
What's that?

386
00:26:39,140 --> 00:26:40,540
I did it...

387
00:26:40,540 --> 00:26:41,100
What?

388
00:26:41,100 --> 00:26:43,580
I finally did it... This is it!

389
00:26:47,040 --> 00:26:52,300
This reaction...
I've waited thirty years for this.

390
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:57,970
I did it, Chopper!
I've completed my research!

391
00:26:57,970 --> 00:27:01,350
I wasn't wrong! I wasn't! I wasn't!

392
00:27:10,650 --> 00:27:16,110
Now I can make cherry blossoms
bloom on this winter island!

393
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:24,550
Listen. I'm going out,
but you stay put and rest here.

394
00:27:24,550 --> 00:27:25,420
Okay.

395
00:27:25,420 --> 00:27:26,780
See you later!

396
00:27:28,690 --> 00:27:30,880
Doctor was happy...

397
00:27:30,880 --> 00:27:36,340
I was able... to cure
someone's sickness!

398
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:37,720
Huh?

399
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:40,390
You'll make a fine doctor!

400
00:27:40,390 --> 00:27:42,390
I'm living proof of that.

401
00:27:47,570 --> 00:27:51,650
Did you know that the entire country
has a screw loose?

402
00:27:51,650 --> 00:27:53,360
Yeah, I know.

403
00:27:53,360 --> 00:27:57,880
It's over the Issie 20
falling ill, right? Ridiculous!

404
00:27:57,880 --> 00:28:00,750
So... what brought you here today?

405
00:28:00,750 --> 00:28:03,830
Actually, I have a favor to ask.

406
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:03,830
Don't bother, I refuse.

407
00:28:03,830 --> 00:28:05,790
I haven't asked anything yet!

408
00:28:05,790 --> 00:28:08,980
What's this dust?

409
00:28:08,980 --> 00:28:10,690
That is the fruit of thirty years.

410
00:28:10,690 --> 00:28:13,450
It's a medicine I've finally completed—

411
00:28:13,450 --> 00:28:16,470
a cure-all that can mend
this country's sick heart.

412
00:28:16,470 --> 00:28:20,600
What a waste of thirty years.
Well, good for you.

413
00:28:20,600 --> 00:28:22,930
So, why are you showing it to me?

414
00:28:22,930 --> 00:28:25,840
There isn't enough dust,
and I'm out of time.

415
00:28:25,840 --> 00:28:28,440
I want you to make
the cherry blossoms bloom.

416
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:30,680
That's absurd! Why do I have to–

417
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:30,690
And one more thing!

418
00:28:30,690 --> 00:28:32,900
Please teach medicine to Chopper.

419
00:28:32,900 --> 00:28:35,360
He wants to become a doctor.

420
00:28:35,360 --> 00:28:36,600
That's enough!

421
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:39,070
He's a reindeer and a monster,

422
00:28:36,950 --> 00:28:38,340
Why would I...?

423
00:28:39,070 --> 00:28:41,070
but I know he'll make a fine doctor!

424
00:28:41,070 --> 00:28:43,360
He's a good kid with a kind heart.

425
00:28:43,360 --> 00:28:46,290
He risked his life
to make a remedy for me!

426
00:28:46,290 --> 00:28:49,620
Please! Help him become a doctor!

427
00:28:49,620 --> 00:28:51,630
You have some nerve!

428
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:56,290
You want me to take care of your
stupid research and strange pet?!

429
00:28:56,290 --> 00:28:58,470
You should know I'm not someone

430
00:28:58,470 --> 00:29:01,550
who'll sympathize with a man
just because he's about to croak!

431
00:29:01,550 --> 00:29:03,720
Get out of here!

432
00:29:07,270 --> 00:29:12,280
Yeah... I know... We've
known each other a long time.

433
00:29:14,870 --> 00:29:16,150
I'm counting on you.

434
00:29:16,150 --> 00:29:20,910
It's not like you, Hiriluk...
throwing in the towel already.

435
00:29:20,910 --> 00:29:23,370
I'm out of time.

436
00:29:23,370 --> 00:29:24,910
That idiot! He wouldn't!

437
00:29:24,910 --> 00:29:26,420
What do you mean?!

438
00:29:26,420 --> 00:29:28,150
The Issie 20 fell ill!

439
00:29:28,150 --> 00:29:29,660
Who'll treat our people now?!

440
00:29:29,660 --> 00:29:31,750
At least give us access to medicine!

441
00:29:31,750 --> 00:29:33,130
There's nothing we can do!

442
00:29:31,790 --> 00:29:35,340
Ropeway Station Four

443
00:29:33,130 --> 00:29:35,350
Even doctors get sick!

444
00:29:33,560 --> 00:29:34,900
Out of my way!

445
00:29:34,900 --> 00:29:36,710
Ahh! Hiriluk?!

446
00:29:35,350 --> 00:29:36,710
Out of my way! Out of my way!

447
00:29:39,170 --> 00:29:41,380
That bastard is crazy!

448
00:29:41,380 --> 00:29:43,540
Prepare the ropeway.

449
00:29:43,540 --> 00:29:45,680
Take me to the castle.

450
00:29:46,640 --> 00:29:48,610
Where's Hiriluk?!

451
00:29:48,610 --> 00:29:52,190
You don't have to run away!
I know about you!

452
00:29:52,190 --> 00:29:55,150
I'm asking you where the quack went!

453
00:29:55,150 --> 00:29:59,110
D-Doctor got better,
so he went to town...

454
00:29:59,610 --> 00:30:02,460
Got better? There's no
getting better for him.

455
00:30:02,460 --> 00:30:04,720
Modern medicine can't help him.

456
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:06,580
That's not true! Look at this!

457
00:30:07,590 --> 00:30:09,790
He's fine now because he ate this!

458
00:30:09,790 --> 00:30:12,500
That's... an amiudake!

459
00:30:12,500 --> 00:30:15,900
This is a cure-all!
So he's fine now!

460
00:30:15,900 --> 00:30:17,960
Doctor said that he felt better, too!

461
00:30:17,960 --> 00:30:20,700
He's going to teach me
how to be a doct–

462
00:30:28,680 --> 00:30:30,390
What was that for?!

463
00:30:31,390 --> 00:30:34,060
You stupid reindeer!

464
00:30:34,060 --> 00:30:36,810
That mushroom is...

465
00:30:36,810 --> 00:30:39,000
That mushroom is...

466
00:30:43,620 --> 00:30:44,990
a deadly poison!

467
00:30:45,790 --> 00:30:49,260
Once you eat it,
you'll be dead within half a day!

468
00:30:49,260 --> 00:30:49,950
What?

469
00:30:52,560 --> 00:30:55,320
That's why that idiot...

470
00:30:56,270 --> 00:31:01,040
That can't be true.
I looked it up in a book...

471
00:31:01,040 --> 00:31:03,240
although I lost that book...

472
00:31:03,240 --> 00:31:04,930
That mushroom can beat diseases!

473
00:31:05,970 --> 00:31:09,550
That's why I raised this skull
and crossbones against all diseases!

474
00:31:09,550 --> 00:31:14,390
That's right! There was a skull
next to the amiudake picture!

475
00:31:14,390 --> 00:31:17,400
Doctor also said he got better!

476
00:31:17,400 --> 00:31:20,730
There's no way he'll die! You're a liar!

477
00:31:21,530 --> 00:31:24,150
Paddle faster! Hurry up!

478
00:31:24,700 --> 00:31:27,200
There isn't a second to waste!

479
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:30,500
What you did touched him deeply.

480
00:31:30,500 --> 00:31:33,100
But the skull in the book
indicates poison.

481
00:31:33,100 --> 00:31:33,670
That's a lie!

482
00:31:33,670 --> 00:31:36,370
It's not a lie! Remember this:

483
00:31:36,370 --> 00:31:39,780
No one medicine in this world
can possibly cure every disease.

484
00:31:39,780 --> 00:31:41,780
That's why doctors exist!

485
00:31:41,780 --> 00:31:42,710
That's not true!

486
00:31:42,710 --> 00:31:46,260
Listen. You can't save people
just by being kind!

487
00:31:46,260 --> 00:31:50,010
If you want to save them,
learn medical knowledge and skills!

488
00:31:50,790 --> 00:31:53,470
Without these skills,
you can't save anyone!

489
00:32:03,640 --> 00:32:04,860
You idiot.

490
00:32:16,250 --> 00:32:18,950
King Wapol! Hiriluk is
heading to this castle!

491
00:32:18,950 --> 00:32:21,190
So he took the bait!

492
00:32:21,190 --> 00:32:23,130
What a hippo!

493
00:32:23,130 --> 00:32:27,090
Is he serious? Why? What for?

494
00:32:28,430 --> 00:32:30,760
He's not returning to this house.

495
00:32:31,860 --> 00:32:34,470
He's gone to make
the castle his graveyard.

496
00:32:36,330 --> 00:32:40,480
Take me to the patients!
I came to save the Issie 20!

497
00:32:43,640 --> 00:32:44,500
What?

498
00:32:45,980 --> 00:32:49,350
What a hippo! You still don't get it?!

499
00:32:49,350 --> 00:32:54,030
It was a trap! As you can see,
the Issie 20 are just fine!

500
00:32:56,450 --> 00:33:00,540
Your only purpose here
is to die, Dr. Hiriluk.

501
00:33:01,330 --> 00:33:03,170
Why did he come here?

502
00:33:06,340 --> 00:33:07,970
Guards, ready...

503
00:33:13,140 --> 00:33:14,060
That's all it was?

504
00:33:16,040 --> 00:33:19,850
Good... So none of them are sick?

505
00:33:22,180 --> 00:33:26,220
I was convinced that
this was a national crisis.

506
00:33:26,220 --> 00:33:29,530
But it was merely a trick...

507
00:33:30,660 --> 00:33:35,360
Hmph! If it really was a crisis,
I wouldn't want someone like you!

508
00:33:35,360 --> 00:33:37,500
But I digress. Execute him!

509
00:33:37,500 --> 00:33:42,580
Don't bother. You can't kill me.

510
00:33:42,580 --> 00:33:43,420
Huh?

511
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:48,420
Hey... when do you think
a person dies?

512
00:33:51,680 --> 00:33:54,750
When a pistol's bullet
pierces their heart?

513
00:33:54,750 --> 00:33:56,300
No.

514
00:33:56,300 --> 00:33:58,850
When they're stricken
with an incurable disease?

515
00:33:58,850 --> 00:34:00,850
No.

516
00:34:00,850 --> 00:34:03,060
When they eat
a poisonous mushroom soup?

517
00:34:03,060 --> 00:34:04,900
No!

518
00:34:06,720 --> 00:34:10,280
A person dies...
when they are forgotten.

519
00:34:12,200 --> 00:34:15,930
Even if I disappear,
my dream will come true.

520
00:34:15,930 --> 00:34:19,410
The people's sickness of the heart
will be cured as well.

521
00:34:20,410 --> 00:34:23,620
Why are you crying... Dalton?

522
00:34:25,210 --> 00:34:28,130
I'm wondering... if this country
will be cured as well.

523
00:34:29,410 --> 00:34:32,090
Of course. If someone is willing
to carry it forward.

524
00:34:32,090 --> 00:34:35,300
Now, now, Dalton!
What are you crying for?

525
00:34:38,860 --> 00:34:45,370
Soon a monster will arrive.
He's my son. Don't hurt him.

526
00:34:47,900 --> 00:34:55,030
Don't worry, Chopper.
Your mushroom can't kill me.

527
00:34:56,160 --> 00:34:59,330
What a marvelous life it's been!

528
00:35:00,750 --> 00:35:02,330
Goodbye, quack...

529
00:35:04,080 --> 00:35:07,340
Thank you, Chopper!

530
00:35:28,800 --> 00:35:34,990
He blew himself up! What a hippo!

531
00:35:41,180 --> 00:35:41,700
Ahh!

532
00:35:41,700 --> 00:35:42,660
What's that?!

533
00:35:42,660 --> 00:35:43,660
It's a monster!

534
00:35:43,660 --> 00:35:44,600
Shoot it!

535
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:46,080
Ahh!

536
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:48,690
Wait!

537
00:35:51,990 --> 00:35:55,860
Leave. Get out of here!

538
00:35:55,860 --> 00:35:58,560
How can you possibly defeat them...

539
00:35:58,560 --> 00:36:01,560
when you can't even beat me?!

540
00:36:02,430 --> 00:36:05,770
I apologize on behalf of all those
who laughed at Hiriluk's death,

541
00:36:08,600 --> 00:36:11,730
but you'll needlessly join him
if you fight them in this state.

542
00:36:13,570 --> 00:36:19,140
This country has seen
enough sacrifices for one day.

543
00:36:20,110 --> 00:36:21,580
Please...

544
00:36:21,580 --> 00:36:22,740
Huh?

545
00:36:27,450 --> 00:36:28,750
You let him flee, Dalton.

546
00:36:28,750 --> 00:36:31,850
Shut up! You still don't get it?

547
00:36:31,850 --> 00:36:36,460
The only man who tried to save
this sick country has just died.

548
00:36:36,460 --> 00:36:38,460
When everyone
gave up and despaired,

549
00:36:38,460 --> 00:36:41,200
a kind doctor died
trying to save this country!

550
00:36:41,200 --> 00:36:44,270
So what if someone like that dies?

551
00:36:44,270 --> 00:36:48,270
I see now where the kingdom is headed,
so it's best if it dies too.

552
00:36:48,270 --> 00:36:51,770
With us at the helm, it can't be rebuilt.

553
00:36:51,770 --> 00:36:53,510
Even if medical care progresses...

554
00:36:53,510 --> 00:36:55,650
even if medical research continues...

555
00:36:57,050 --> 00:36:59,740
no amount of medicine
can cure a fool!

556
00:37:00,750 --> 00:37:07,370
I let you speak your mind...
and it's made me extremely angry!

557
00:37:10,190 --> 00:37:14,170
Please... please teach me
to be a doctor!

558
00:37:14,170 --> 00:37:19,870
Please... teach me to be a doctor!
I'll become the cure-all!

559
00:37:19,870 --> 00:37:24,870
I'll become a doctor who can
cure anything. I'll even cure a country!

560
00:37:24,870 --> 00:37:26,680
Because... Because...

561
00:37:26,680 --> 00:37:31,150
there's no disease that can't be cured!

562
00:37:37,720 --> 00:37:41,840
You can call me... Doctorine.

563
00:37:45,930 --> 00:37:49,830
I won't... die here.

564
00:37:49,830 --> 00:37:53,000
I will carry on his will.

565
00:37:56,840 --> 00:38:02,110
So for the last six years...
Tony has been studying under you.

566
00:38:02,110 --> 00:38:08,250
Yeah... I taught him
everything I know.

567
00:38:08,250 --> 00:38:09,890
Doctorine! Doctorine!

568
00:38:11,630 --> 00:38:13,350
Doctorine! There's a problem!

569
00:38:13,980 --> 00:38:15,650
Wapol is back!

570
00:38:18,090 --> 00:38:19,360
Is that so...

571
00:38:19,360 --> 00:38:21,110
Ah! That bastard!

572
00:38:22,660 --> 00:38:24,990
It's that big mouth!

573
00:38:28,970 --> 00:38:31,540
Look! Everything is just how I left it!

574
00:38:31,540 --> 00:38:34,560
Let's get back to my castle
and restore the Kingdom of Drum!

575
00:38:37,410 --> 00:38:40,550
Just a moment, King Wapol!
On top of the castle...

576
00:38:40,550 --> 00:38:41,260
Huh?

577
00:38:46,350 --> 00:38:48,890
What's that strange flag?

578
00:38:48,890 --> 00:38:51,310
What happened to Drum's royal flag?!

579
00:38:55,130 --> 00:38:57,400
I burned that thing.

580
00:38:57,950 --> 00:39:02,140
So you show yourself, Dr. Kureha,
the last survivor of the doctor hunt!

581
00:39:02,140 --> 00:39:04,710
This castle is no longer yours!

582
00:39:04,710 --> 00:39:08,620
This isn't a place
for rotten brats like you!

583
00:39:08,620 --> 00:39:13,330
Leave this country!
The Kingdom of Drum has already died out!

584
00:39:14,180 --> 00:39:16,040
What'd you say?!

585
00:39:17,710 --> 00:39:18,670
Wait!

586
00:39:20,710 --> 00:39:23,880
I'm gonna beat the crap outta him!
